300 g Tilapia
2 unit(s) Sandwich Bun
6 g Caribbean Spice Blend
170 g Coleslaw Cabbage Mix
7 g Cilantro
28 g Spring Mix
43 mL Sour Cream
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
1 tbsp Seasoned Rice Vinegar
90 mL Dill Pickle, sliced
1 tbsp Butter*
1 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the broiler to high.
Wash and dry all produce.
Roughly chop cilantro.
In a large bowl, drain pickle juice, set pickles aside. Add coleslaw cabbage mix, vinegar, mayo, sour cream, cilantro and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar. Season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat.

Brush a foil-lined baking sheet with 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil.
Pat tilapia dry with paper towels, pressing well to absorb as much moisture as possible.
Arrange tilapia on prepared baking sheet. Season with salt, pepper and Carribean Spice Blend. Drizzle 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil over top.
Broil in the middle of the oven for 7-9 min, until cooked through.**

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
While pan heats, halve buns.
When the pan is hot, add 1 tbsp butter. Swirl the pan for 30 sec until butter melts. Add buns cut-sides down. Reduce heat to medium. (NOTE: For 4 servings, toast buns in batches, using 1 tbsp butter per batch.)
Using another pan or a spatula, gently press down on buns and toast for 2-3 min per side, until crisp and golden.

Stack bottom buns with spring mix, tilapia, some of the slaw and some of the pickles. Close with top buns.
Serve any remaining slaw and any remaining pickles on the side.